The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi,July 2: Finance minister Pranab Mukherjee is likely to meet state finance ministers on July 21 to discuss constitutional amendments needed to roll out goods and services tax (GST) and the compensation package for states for any possible revenue loss they suffer because of the implementation of GST.                            
	 New Delhi,July 2: The government, which expects the national highway toll collection to jump to Rs 10,000 crore in four years, plans to put in place a new electronic toll collection system to plug revenue losses by the middle of 2012.                             
	 New Delhi,July 2: The mutual fund industry saw a sharp decline in its average assets in June as withdrawals offset gains from an upward move in the equity market. The average assets under management of the 39 fund houses plunged Rs 1.27 lakh crore, or 16 per cent, in June.                            
	 Mumbai, July 2: Tata Consultancy Services is planning to hire around 30,000 employees this fiscal. TCS has 1,60,000 employees and had added 16,851 professionals in the fourth quarter of the last fiscal.                            
	 New Delhi, July 2: PowerGrids board has approved a proposal for a 20 per cent follow-on public offer to raise funds for expansion. The Centre plans to offload 10 per cent of its stake and the firm will raise an equal percentage of fresh equity.                                                                                                                          
